AWS Lambda and CloudWatch Integration Task

Objective:
The objective of this task was to understand how AWS Lambda works with Amazon CloudWatch for backend execution monitoring and logging.

Services Used:
• AWS Lambda
• Amazon CloudWatch
• Node.js Runtime

STEP 1: Created AWS Lambda Function

Opened AWS Lambda Console.
Created a new Lambda function.
Selected Node.js runtime.
Configured the Lambda environment.
Created the function successfully.

Learning:
AWS Lambda is a serverless compute service used to execute backend code without managing servers.

STEP 2: Added Lambda Code

Added Node.js code inside the Lambda function.
Created a variable to store a value.
Used console.log() to print output.
Added response handling using statusCode and body.
Deployed the Lambda code successfully.

Learning:
Lambda executes backend logic and console.log() is used for logging and debugging.

STEP 3: Tested Lambda Function

Created a test event.
Executed the Lambda function using the Test option.
Initially received a runtime/module error.
Reviewed execution logs for debugging.
Identified syntax issue related to ES module configuration.

Error Observed:
exports is not defined in ES module scope

Learning:
Cloud applications often require debugging and log analysis during development.

STEP 4: Debugged and Fixed the Error

Modified the export syntax in the code.
Updated CommonJS syntax to ES module syntax.
Redeployed the corrected code.
Re-executed the Lambda function.
Verified successful execution.

Learning:
Correct runtime syntax is required for successful Lambda execution.

STEP 5: Successful Lambda Execution

Lambda function executed successfully.
Received successful HTTP response.
Verified statusCode 200 response.
Verified returned output value.
Confirmed successful backend execution.

Successful Response:

{
"statusCode": 200,
"body": ""Hello from AWS Lambda""
}

Learning:
StatusCode 200 confirms successful execution of the Lambda function.

STEP 6: Verified CloudWatch Logs

Opened the Monitor tab in AWS Lambda.
Accessed CloudWatch Logs.
Opened the latest log stream.
Verified console log output.
Checked Lambda execution details.

Verified Output:
INFO Fetched Value: Hello from AWS Lambda

Learning:
Amazon CloudWatch automatically stores Lambda execution logs for monitoring and troubleshooting.

Integration Understanding

Service                     Purpose

AWS Lambda             Executes backend/serverless code
CloudWatch             Stores logs and monitoring data
IAM                     Controls permissions and access
Node.js Runtime         Executes JavaScript backend code

Main Purpose of the Task

The primary objective of this task was to understand:

• Serverless backend execution
• Lambda function testing
• Error debugging
• Console log monitoring
• CloudWatch integration with Lambda
• Backend monitoring workflow

Final Outcome

Successfully created, executed, debugged, and monitored an AWS Lambda function using Amazon CloudWatch logs.
